purpose of background script:
    communicate information from outside webpages to your extension code.
purpose of content script:
    pass information to your extension when user is not on your page.  

when a user moves to a new webpage, the content script will send sender info to background script. (tabID and tab URL and favIconUrl)

background script will cross check the tab URL against tileList (chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener function)
    If match is found:
        background script will send tab information to portals
            - tabID (sender.tab.id)
            - tabURL (sender.url)
            - favIconUrl (sender.tab.favIconUrl)
            - sitetitle (sender.tab.title)
        
        portals will check if item is missing favicon and/or screenshot
            if missing:
                portals will pull info using tabID, and update localStorage with the new information
            if not missing:
                portals will check last updated time for that item in tileList
                    if time > time limit (3 days):
                        portals will pull info using tabID, and update localStorage with new information

Next steps:
- update manifest.json to include content scripts
- write a content script that will send the tab URL to background 
- write the background script that will have an event listener for messages from content scripts 
- write a whole bunch of conditionals for background script


